<?xml version="1.0"?>
<article xmlns="http://www.thomasoandrews.com/xmlns/bridge"
         xmlns:check="http://www.thomasoandrews.com/xmlns/checklink">
<title>Test All Links</title>
<body>
<p>These are all the links from my articles.  This is a cool feature of
XML - the ability to extract all objects by type.  Here, I can
test all my links from my article sets on this one page, rather than
checking them on their original context.  It would be even better
if XSL could just check for the link rot...</p>
<check:article file="everybody"/>
<check:articles dir="test"/>
<check:articles dir="badfit"/>
<check:articles dir="hands"/>
<check:articles dir="parzero"/>
<check:articles dir="tenaces"/>
</body>
</article>
